<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871030-0027 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Big Bear Inc.</HL><DD> 10/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BGBRTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   A group including three officers of Butler Capital Corp., a New York-based investment banking firm, said it holds a 5.9% stake in Big Bear Inc.'s common shares outstanding and may seek a more active role in the Columbus, Ohio-based supermarket operator.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the group said it holds 460,750 Big Bear common shares, including 73,000 shares purchased from Oct. 22 to Monday for $19 to $19.25 a share.    Big Bear shares closed yesterday at $19, up 50 cents, in national over-the-counter trading.    The group said it purchased the Big Bear shares for investment purposes but may try to &quot;explore&quot; with the company a possible merger, board representation, asset sales or other actions.    Big Bear officials couldn't be reached for comment. </TEXT></DOC>